window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>What do you become when your father’s a centaur and your mother’s a powerful magician? A unicorn shifter…</b></p> <p>You’d think being the only known unicorn shifter in the world would have a few benefits, like people treating you kindly or getting special treatment from the council. Not in my case. I'd be lucky to get a piece of bread thrown at me.</p> <p>My name is Celestia Rainbow, and, yes, my last name is f---king Rainbow.</p> <p>Shifters assume that I’m kind by nature, but trust me, I’m not. I’m fierce, short-tempered, and have the mouth of a sailor. Add in my stealthy fighting skills, advanced magic casting, and swift movement you’ll soon realize I'm someone you wouldn't want to mess with. But everyone seems to only look at my shifter side—my ditzy peaceful half, sprinkling magic dust and on a mission to end world hunger.</p> <p>Regardless of my dual personality, I’ve sworn to become a huntress at Aslan Academy. Now that I’m of age—my lucky twenty-fifth birthday just happens to coincide with the entrance exams—I’m ready to prove my worth.</p> <p>Too bad I’ve been grouped up with six sinfully attractive men.</p> <p>Time to prove to my community, classmates, and this attractive bunch of weirdos that unicorns can kick ass too.</p>"; 
